msgid "English markdown is the only source maintained by humans. Translations live in `docs/book/po/<locale>.po` files that act as a cache, and `cargo mdbook sync` keeps them current. Routine English docs PRs do not need to carry the generated `.po` churn: leave it for a dedicated translation-cache PR. For the full translation pipeline (app strings, docs, zerocode, adding a locale, release passes), see [Docs & Translations](../maintainers/docs-and-translations.md)."
